OL,3,CDaughter of Ozzy Osbourne mourns her
OL,4,Cfather 'every day' a year after death
OL,6,FOsbourne also said she wishes her
OL,7,Ffather could see "the little man" her
OL,8,Fson Sidney is becoming, adding: "Every
OL,9,Fsingle day I catch glimpses of you in
OL,10,Fhim. Your smile. Your spirit. Your
OL,11,Fmannerisms.
OL,13,F"Sometimes it stops me in my tracks
OL,14,Fbecause it feels as though you've
OL,15,Ffound a way to remind me that love
OL,16,Fnever truly leaves us.
OL,18,F"Seeing you reflected in him is one of
OL,19,Fthe greatest gifts I have ever been
OL,20,Fgiven."
OL,26,@oD@ROUoD@aO]pD@aOUuD@AOUzD@AOU|D@GO]
